¬†
Ent√£o, para esclarecer, essas obras n√£o estavam paralisadas. Elas encontravam-se a todo vapor no Governo Bolsonaro e n√£o foram entregues no ano passado, porque muitas obras no Brasil tiveram atrasos, por causa da pandemia de Covid-19.¬†

The Minister of Transport, Renan Filho, was last Friday (24) in Esp√≠rito Santo.He came to visit some structuring works here from our state, such as the outline of Master √Ålvaro and the stretch that connects the Port of Vit√≥ria (Cais de Capuaba) to BR-262.These two works are only possible, because I am the author of their federalization through two laws.That is, I am the father of those two works.

Com o corpo em chamas, Heley ainda tirou as crian√ßas pela janela da sala de aula. Outras duas funcion√°rias a ajudaram no ato de bravura: J√©ssica Morgana e Geni Oliveira, que tamb√©m faleceram.

A principal homenageada do dia, a mulher do ano: irm√£ Ilda, que tem dentro do cora√ß√£o uma f√© inabal√°vel em Deus e em nosso pa√≠s, sendo uma verdadeira coluna de ora√ß√£o dando suporte a todos os patriotas que estavam e continuam presos. Outras grandes mulheres que tive a honra de homenagear foram Kamila Mendon√ßa, diretora do pres√≠dio feminino de Bras√≠lia, e toda sua equipe. Professor Heley de Abreu, who has shown that courage and love for others can be brought to the last consequences by saving children from a coward attack at a school in Jana√∫ba - MG.With his body on fire, Heley still took the children through the classroom window.Two other employees helped her in the act of bravery: Jessica Morgana and Geni Oliveira, who also died.

Daughter letter to father.

Dad I owe you so much that if you wanted to thank you for everything in detail I would have to stay days and days thanking.Besides gratitude, my respect, admiration and love are also yours.

Since I was a child I closely follow almost your entire life trajectory, there are so many stories, achievements, battles you have faced and will face.Know that I will be by your side and God will be with you in every step.

It's years and years watching you fight for big causes and even in the face of adversity, a lot of tiredness you have never lost faith.

We approved a few days ago, with a strong opposition from the left, our Bill No. 1,180-A of 2022 which aims to help children and adolescents from Rio's public schools to enjoy the various public services of the city consciously and respectfully.

There is a gigantic difficulty when trying to modify tremendously harmful negative standards for years in Brazil and in each of its thousands of municipalities, all always at an unbelievable cost and always with strong and orchestrated opposition of PT and PSOL.

It is a scandalously glaring fact that in Brazil has become a tradition burning bus, depredating stations, shattering glass windows (as done in Fiesp a few years ago) and vandalizing public and private assets in every way possible and imaginable as often as it is not seen inmore developed countries.

Nothing better than showing children and adolescents than the destruction of what is of all harms not others, but all, including those who perpetrate vandalisms.And the school can be a complement to the family in this sense, teaching values for harmonic, civilized and prosperous coexistence.

There are few, for example, cases of systematic depredation in BRT stations and Rio buses, depredations that generate huge and constant damage to the public purse, to the pocket of the tax -paying citizen.How about stopping schools to train militants and train citizens?

Unfortunately, the project was vetoed by the mayor, who did not get sensitized about his merits (if he thought the project needed improvements, its government leader could have presented the proper amendments and make it more appropriate to the needs of the city during the processvoting).

We can only expect the Rio Chamber, with this new configuration in 2023, topple the veto and that the city reconsider its position allowing it to be promulgated and applied.
